# Default Avatar Placeholder

This is a placeholder for the default avatar image that will be shown if no profile picture is uploaded or if the uploaded image fails to load.

## Recommended Default Avatar Options:

1. **Generic Avatar Icon**: A simple user silhouette or icon
2. **Initials Avatar**: Circle with user's initials (A.J. for Alex Johnson)
3. **Abstract Pattern**: Geometric pattern or gradient
4. **Professional Placeholder**: Clean, minimal design

## Implementation:

You can replace this text file with an actual image file:
- `default-avatar.jpg`
- `default-avatar.png` 
- `default-avatar.svg`

## SVG Example (save as default-avatar.svg):

```svg
<svg width="200" height="200" viewBox="0 0 200 200" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <defs>
    <linearGradient id="grad" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="100%">
      <stop offset="0%" style="stop-color:#3b82f6;stop-opacity:1" />
      <stop offset="100%" style="stop-color:#10b981;stop-opacity:1" />
    </linearGradient>
  </defs>
  <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="100" fill="url(#grad)"/>
  <text x="100" y="120" font-family="Inter, sans-serif" font-size="60" font-weight="600" text-anchor="middle" fill="white">AJ</text>
</svg>
```

This creates a gradient circle with the initials "AJ" for Alex Johnson.

## Alternative: CSS-Generated Avatar

You can also create avatars programmatically using CSS and JavaScript libraries like:
- **Boring Avatars**: Generate SVG avatars
- **Dicebear**: API for generating avatars
- **Gravatar**: Email-based avatars
- **UI Avatars**: Text-based avatars

The About component will automatically fall back to this default image if the main profile image fails to load.